
{center}
{subhead} Randomise Announce New Amiga Computers{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

Randomise Inc. have announced several new Amiga computers, starting with a
'060 based machine, a PowerPC machine, an Amiga for Mac users with the Fusion
Apple Mac emulator, and a new Toaster compatible machine.
{p} {p}
Details on the '060 version, which hold for the other machines, are:
{p} {p}
  True Colour Graphics and PC Monitor compatibility just to name a few!{p}
  AmigaOS 3.1 with preemptive multitasking{p}
  Motorola 68060 50 Mhz{p}
  16 MB RAM optionally expandable to 128 MB{p}
  24-bit Retargetable 2MB Graphics Board provides 800x600 in 24-Bit{p}
  3.2 GB IDE harddisk{p}
  32x IDE CD-Rom{p}
  Low Density Floppy Disk Drive - 720KB PC format compatible{p}
  Compatible with any Standard PC-type Multisync Montior{p}
  Windows95 Keyboard Compatible - 104 Windows95 Keyboard Included{p}
  AGA Graphics System included on board{p}
      Video and Genlock capable{p}
  4-Channel Stereo Sound standard, each 8 Bit DMA{p}
  Interfaces:{p}
   1 x serial RS-232c (modem),{p}
   1 x parallel (printer),{p}
   1 x external floppy drive,{p}
   2 x mouse/joystick,{p}
   1 x 23 pin video RGB (monitor) output from AGA Chipset,{p}
   1 x 15 pin video RGB (monitor) output from 24-Bit Graphics Board,{p}
   1 x video composite (TV, video recorder),{p}
   1 x RF modulator (TV antenna),{p}
   2 x stereo audio{p}
  250 Watt Power Supply{p}
  Personal Paint 7.1 CD - Full Version - To get you working quickly!{p}
  Full Documentation For AmigaOS 3.1, and hardware{p}
{p} {p}
  System Price - $1649.95 US, $2524.95 CDN{p}
{p} {p}
  Optional Fast SCSI Controler - Add to System Price $134.95 CDN, $94.95 US{p}